# SQL Style

- Follow dbt-style formatting with named CTE steps.
- Avoid subqueries; use CTEs instead.
- Do not use shortened aliases (for example `u`, `a`, `c`).
- Use descriptive snake_case names for CTEs and selected fields.
- Prefer explicit select lists in final result queries.
